{"session_id": 48, "bill_id": 14239, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 41, "bill_title": "revise and repeal certain provisions requiring court appearances for violations of game, fish and parks statutes.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Court", "Promise to Appear"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 14239, "bill_version_id": 80174, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1999-01-09T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to revise and repeal certain provisions requiring court appearances for violations of game, fish and parks statutes. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 41-15-11 be amended to read as follows: 41-15-11. Except as otherwise specifically provided, whenever If any resident is arrested for a violation of any provision of this title, punishable as a misdemeanor, the arresting officer shall take the name and address of the person and information relative to the violation and issue him the person a summons in writing to appear at a time and place, the time to be within five days after the arrest unless the person arrested demands an earlier hearing in court . The officer shall release the person from custody upon receiving from him the person a written promise to appear at the time and place designated by the officer. A nonresident arrested for a violation of chapter 41-9, fishing, hunting , or trapping on private land, shall be required to post bond in the amount set forth on the fine and bond schedule provided by the presiding circuit court judge, or in an amount set by a magistrate or judge for that offense, before being released from custody. A nonresident arrested for any other violation of the provisions of this title, except chapter 41-9, may be required to post bond in the amount outlined above before being released from custody. Any person who intentionally violates his the written promise to appear, given in accordance with the provisions of this section, is guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor. Section 2. That \u00a7 41-15-12 be repealed. 41-15-12. Any person arrested for a violation of any provision of this title, punishable as a misdemeanor or petty offense, shall, if he so desires, have a right to an immediate hearing or a hearing within twenty-four hours at a convenient hour, and such hearing to be before a magistrate within the county wherein such offense was committed."}, {"bill_id": 14239, "bill_version_id": 80173, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "1999-02-09T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 14239, "action_date": "1999-01-12T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 81769, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/81769.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 22, "committee_id_action": 629, "committee_id_assigned": 607, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 14239, "action_date": "1999-01-22T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 82052, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/82052.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 607, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 14239, "action_date": "1999-01-22T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 82052, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/82052.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 155, "committee_id_action": 607, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 42477, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [2225, 2230, 2234, 2269, 2270, 2215, 2299]}}, {"bill_id": 14239, "action_date": "1999-01-25T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 82143, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/82143.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 183, "committee_id_action": 629, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 42542, "president_vote": null, 